4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, the trustees on the Board of
6 Trustees of the University of Montevallo are appointed
7 for terms of 12 years, and five members of the board
8 constitutes a quorum for meetings.
9 This bill would revise the term of office for
10 trustees and would place a limit on how many terms
11 trustees may serve.
12 This bill would revise the number of members of
13 the board that constitutes a quorum.
14 Also under existing law, to qualify for
15 appointment, the President of the University of
16 Montevallo must be an educator by profession.
17 This bill would remove the requirement that the
18 president of the university must be an educator by
19 profession.
20 This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
21 technical revisions to update the existing code
22 language to current style.
23
24
25 A BILL
26 TO BE ENTITLED
27 AN ACT
