HB164 INTRODUCED
29
30 Relating to the University of Montevallo; to amend
31 Sections 16-54-2, and 16-54-5, Code of Alabama 1975; to revise
32 the terms of office of the Board of Trustees of the University
33 of Montevallo; to revise the number of board members that
34 constitutes a quorum; to remove the requirement that the
35 president of the university must be an educator by profession;
36 and to make nonsubstantive, technical revisions to update the
37 existing code language to current style.
38 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
39 Section 1. Sections 16-54-2, and 16-54-5 of the Code of
40 Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
41 "§16-54-2
42 The University of Montevallo shall be governed by a
43 board of trustees composed of the Governor, who shall be
44 president, ex officio, the State Superintendent of Education,
45 ex officio, and 11 other trustees ( as follows: (i) one from
46 each congressional district,; (ii) up to one at-large trustee
47 who is not a resident of this state,; and, (iii) until as
48 otherwise herein provided, a number of trustees from the
49 state-at-large sufficient to bring the number to or keep it at
50 11). Five Six members of the board shall constitute a quorum.
51 Trustees shall be appointed for a term of 12 years. Beginning
52 January 1, 2027, trustees shall be appointed for a term of
53 eight years. No trustee shall serve more than two terms on the
54 board of trustees. In case of the creation and establishment
55 of an additional congressional district in the state, the
56 state-at-large trustee most recently appointed shall cease
Page 2

state-at-large trustee most recently appointed shall cease
HB164 INTRODUCED
57 automatically to be a trustee from the state-at-large and
58 become for the remainder of the term trustee for the new
59 district. Otherwise, all new appointees, except for a
60 nonresident appointee and the state-at-large appointees, shall
61 be at the time of their appointment, residents of the district
62 for which they are appointed, respectively. All appointments
63 of trustees shall be made by the Governor with the advice and
64 consent of the Senate. In case of a vacancy in the office of
65 trustee, the Governor shall appoint a successor, who shall
66 hold office until the next meeting of the Legislature, when
67 the Governor, by and with the advice and consent of the
68 Senate, shall appoint a trustee, who shall hold office for the
69 unexpired term. A trustee shall be ineligible to be elected by
70 the board of trustees to or otherwise hold any office of the
71 institution where compensation is provided. The trustees are
72 entitled to receive payment of their actual expenses incurred
73 in the discharge of their duties as trustees."
74 "§16-54-5
75 The trustees shall elect a president for a term to be
76 fixed by them, who shall not be removed during the term for
77 which he or she is elected, except for just cause, which shall
78 be explicitly set forth in writing in the minutes of the
79 proceedings of the trustees and approved by a majority of all
80 the trustees. No person individual shall be eligible to the
81 office of president unless he or she is a graduate of some
82 college or university of well known well-known high standing,
83 an educator by profession, of good moral character, and
84 possessing good business and administrative qualifications.
Page 3

possessing good business and administrative qualifications.
HB164 INTRODUCED
85 The trustees are encouraged to consider an individual who is
86 an educator by profession for the position of president. The
87 trustees shall fix the compensation of the president,
88 including such emoluments and prerequisites necessary to carry
89 out the functions of the office."
90 Section 2. This act shall become effective immediately.
